api_list.name: searchContent
api_list.description: The search endpoint provides a powerful way to find Box content. Use the parameters described in this section to control what you search for.

required_parameters.name: query
required_parameters.description: The string to search for. Box matches the search string against object names, descriptions, text contents of files, and other data.

required_parameters.name: accessToken
required_parameters.description: Access token is a data string that enables Box to verify that a request belongs to an authorized session.

optional_parameters.name: scope
optional_parameters.description: The scope on which you want search. Can be user_content for a search limited to the current user or enterprise_content to search an entire enterprise.

optional_parameters.name: updatedAtRange
optional_parameters.description: The date when the item was updated. Specify the date range using RFC3339 timestamps separated by a comma. For example: `2014-05-15T13:35:01-07:00,2014-05-17T13:35:01-07:00. Either the beginning date or the ending date may be empty, but the separating comma is required. For example, if you omit the beginning date, then the ending date must begin with a comma.

optional_parameters.name: sizeRange
optional_parameters.description: Return only files within a stated size range. Specify the range in bytes with lower and upper bounds separated by a comma, like so:lower_bound_size,upper_bound_size, where 1MB is 1,000,000 bytes. You can specify only the lower bound if you end this parameter with a comma. You can specify only the upper bound by placing a comma at the beginning of the number.

optional_parameters.name: createdAtRange
optional_parameters.description: The date when the item was created. Specify the date range using RFC3339 timestamps separated by a comma. For example: `2014-05-15T13:35:01-07:00,2014-05-17T13:35:01-07:00. Either the beginning date or the ending date may be empty, but the separating comma is required. For example, if you omit the beginning date, then the ending date must begin with a comma.

optional_parameters.name: trashContent
optional_parameters.description: Controls whether to search in the trash. The value can be trashed_only or non_trashed_only. Searches without this parameter default to searching non_trashed_only

optional_parameters.name: type
optional_parameters.description: The type of objects you want to include in the search results. The type can be file, folder, or web_link

optional_parameters.name: limit
optional_parameters.description: The maximum number of items to return. The default is 100 and the maximum is 1,000.

optional_parameters.name: offset
optional_parameters.description: The offset of the item at which to begin the response. See offset-based paging for details.

optional_parameters.name: fileExtensions
optional_parameters.description: Limit searches to specific file extensions like pdf,png, or doc. The value can be a single file extension or a comma-delimited list of extensions. For example: png,md,pdf

optional_parameters.name: ownerUserIds
optional_parameters.description: Search for objects by owner. Requires a user ID or a set of comma-delimited user IDs, like so: user_id_1,user_id_2

optional_parameters.name: ancestorFolderIds
optional_parameters.description: Search for the contents of specific folders (and folders within them). Requires a folder ID or a set of comma-delimited folder IDs, like so: folder_id_1,folder_id_2

optional_parameters.name: contentTypes
optional_parameters.description: Search for objects of specified content types. The types can be name, description, file_content, comments, or tags. Requires a content type or a set of comma-delimited content_types, like so: content_type_1,content_type_2

optional_parameters.name: fields
optional_parameters.description: List of fields to include in the response
